description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Open Day for 3rd Year Students, Staff Nurses and ODPs&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We would like to invite you to a Virtual Open Day on Saturday 21st November 2020. This is a fantastic opportunity to explore opportunities with dedicated and committed staff providing clinical care to the South West within an organisation that was rated as ‘Outstanding for Caring’ by the CQC. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have job opportunities available Trustwide and would welcome all applications from those who are available now or due to graduate in 2021.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The event will include presentations about the Trust, virtual tours around the wards and departments and information on development opportunities. It will also consist of an interview and assessment process in order to ensure we find the right role for you within the Trust if successful.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Virtual Interview on the day&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are interested in attending this Recruitment Event, please apply in order for us to allocate you a place and confirm timings of the day and further information.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please remember to specify your &lt;em&gt;3 preferred areas&lt;/em&gt; of work in your supporting information.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We now offer a UHP rotation programme over an 18 month period which you can find out more about on the day. If you are interested in the rotation, please state this as one of your 3 preferred areas of work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note there will be a separate opportunity available for Paediatric and Midwifery applicants later in the year.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
